parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low-pressure fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of a crash, especially when driving at higher speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine runs rough
warning lights and messages are displayed on the instrument panel
the vehicle is unable to be restarted
hesitation at lower RPMs
sluggish acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in providing a remedy for the low-pressure fuel pump failure recall can cause continued safety risks for vehicle owners, leading to potential accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle owners are not notified of a remedy
dealerships are unable to provide a fix
vehicle owners are forced to continue driving a vehicle with a known safety issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaking into the cab of the vehicle
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop in a timely manner.

brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control or fail to stop in a timely manner, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk forward, leading to accidents or loss of control.

or jerks forward

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and misfiring can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or jerk forward, leading to accidents or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the fuel tank cover can cause it to detach, potentially leading to fuel leaks and fires.
symptoms: The fuel tank cover is corroded

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can cause delays and inconvenience to vehicle owners, potentially leading to continued driving of unsafe vehicles.
symptoms: The part to do the recall repair is unavailable
the manufacturer exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.
